subject: p16050730
Findings: AP and lateral views of the chest were reviewed. The heart size is top normal. The mediastinal and hilar contours are unremarkable. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. There is no focal consolidation concerning for pneumonia. Mild prominence of the pulmonary vasculature is consistent with mild pulmonary edema.
